sql:
SELECT AVG(adults) AS average_adult_premium
FROM insurance_premiums
WHERE region = 'Northeast';

SELECT company_id, SUM(adults + seniors + teens + young_adults) AS total_premium
FROM insurance_premiums
GROUP BY company_id;

SELECT adults 
FROM insurance_premiums 
WHERE company_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
The age groups are defined as follows: 
- 'Adults': typically refers to individuals aged 26-64; 
- 'Seniors': typically refers to individuals aged 65 and above; 
- 'Teens': typically refers to individuals aged 13-19; 
- 'Young Adults': typically refers to individuals aged 20-25.

Northeast region refers to the northeastern part of the United States; 
Average premium amounts are the average cost of insurance premiums for adults and seniors; 
Insurance companies are businesses that provide insurance policies.

sql:
SELECT AVG(adults) 
  FROM insurance_premiums 
  WHERE company_id = (SELECT company_id FROM insurance_companies WHERE company_name = 'State Farm');
